race.comment: PARISH PRINCE (3) has gone close to winning a race this season, and his last 2 starts have been on this course for a brace of second-place finishes. He meets an even field, and gets a nice chance to break his duck. YOU CAN CALL ME AL (4) got going late when finishing runner-up at Ascot a fortnight ago, and the step up to a mile for the first time looks to be an ideal next step. He carries 2kg less in a weaker field, and can go one better. CEDAR LEAF (15) will find this easier than any of her 2 starts to date, and stepping up to a mile will definitely suit her. Include in all top 4 combos at a price. VEXATIOUS ROSE (12) has been placed in 6 of her 7 starts, and even though she cops another wide gate, she is a must for all multiples.
